File: A pair of handcuffs seen on a desk. JOHANNESBURG - Six suspects have been arrested for the kidnapping of Lenasia businessman Luqman Kazi, who was taken on Monday. No ransom was paid. WATCH: Crime in SA | Cape Chamber of Commerce raises concern about kidnappings The suspects were found with over R5-million in cash in their possession. Several cellphones, guns, signal jammers, car number plates and the car used for the alleged kidnapping were also seized. The victim is being examined in hospital and an investigation has been opened.